      <memberdef kind="function" id="alerts_8h_1a98b6140a4d21520d639bc81d1f7c08b7" prot="public" static="no" const="no" explicit="no" inline="no" virt="non-virtual">
        <type>int</type>
        <definition>int generate_alerts</definition>
        <argsstring>(const VitalSigns *vitals, Alert *out, int max_out)</argsstring>
        <name>generate_alerts</name>
        <param>
          <type>const <ref refid="struct_vital_signs" kindref="compound">VitalSigns</ref> *</type>
          <declname>vitals</declname>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type><ref refid="struct_alert" kindref="compound">Alert</ref> *</type>
          <declname>out</declname>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type>int</type>
          <declname>max_out</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Generate alert records for every vital sign parameter outside its normal clinical range. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Iterates over all four vital sign parameters in this fixed order:<orderedlist>
<listitem><para>Heart rate</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Blood pressure (systolic / diastolic)</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Temperature</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>SpO2</para>
</listitem></orderedlist>
</para>
<para>For each parameter that is not ALERT_NORMAL, one <ref refid="struct_alert" kindref="compound">Alert</ref> entry is written to <computeroutput>out</computeroutput>. Writing stops when either all parameters have been checked or <computeroutput>max_out</computeroutput> entries have been filled — whichever comes first.</para>
<para><bold>Memory safety:</bold> the function never writes beyond <computeroutput>out[max_out - 1]</computeroutput>. Passing <computeroutput>max_out = 0</computeroutput> is valid and writes nothing.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername direction="in">vitals</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Pointer to a fully populated <ref refid="struct_vital_signs" kindref="compound">VitalSigns</ref> structure. Must not be NULL. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername direction="out">out</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Caller-allocated array to receive <ref refid="struct_alert" kindref="compound">Alert</ref> records. Must hold at least <computeroutput>max_out</computeroutput> elements. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername direction="in">max_out</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Maximum number of <ref refid="struct_alert" kindref="compound">Alert</ref> entries to write.</para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>Number of <ref refid="struct_alert" kindref="compound">Alert</ref> records written to <computeroutput>out</computeroutput> (0 if all parameters are normal, or if max_out == 0).</para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="pre"><para>vitals != NULL </para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="pre"><para>out != NULL || max_out == 0 </para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="post"><para>Return value &lt;= max_out</para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="par"><title>Requirements</title><para>SWR-ALT-001, SWR-ALT-002, SWR-ALT-003, SWR-ALT-004</para>
</simplesect>
Generate alert records for every vital sign parameter outside its normal clinical range.</para>
<para>Internal flow for each parameter:<orderedlist>
<listitem><para>Call the corresponding check_*() function.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>If the result is not ALERT_NORMAL, write an <ref refid="struct_alert" kindref="compound">Alert</ref> record via PUSH_ALERT.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>PUSH_ALERT enforces the max_out cap before writing.</para>
</listitem></orderedlist>
</para>
<para>The PUSH_ALERT macro copies the parameter name with strncpy (max 31 chars<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>null) and formats the message with snprintf (max ALERT_MSG_LEN - 1 chars</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>null), guaranteeing null-termination in both fields. </para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
